<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--PhantomAttack     02-27 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Phantom Attack,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jet Flies Too Low Terrorizing Desert Town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ADELANTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Air Force dispatched investigators
to begin processing damage claims after a fighter jet buzzed a
residential area, causing broken windows, fallen roof tiles and
minor injuries.
   A pilot from Edwards Air Force Base was participating in a
week-long military exercise at George Air Force Base, and was
simulating an attack in an F-4 Phantom fighter when the damage
occurred Thursday afternoon, George spokesmen said.
   ``He probably didn't know the area and didn't know how close we
are to Adelanto,'' Tech. Sgt. Jorge Caballero. The two bases are
more than 50 miles apart in the desert north of Los Angeles.
   ``There were no major injuries, but there were some complaints
of roof tiles falling on people and some minor cuts and scrapes,''
Caballero said.
   The pilot's name was not released.
</TEXT>
