<HEAD>New Book Telling Bush's Religious Side Being Rushed Into Print</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Despite its religious overtones, a new book
telling the spiritual side of Vice President George Bush is not
intended to counter Pat Robertson's challenge in the GOP
presidential race, the publisher says.
   ``We want people to know that George Bush is a Christian but
he's more than a Christian. He has great political experience,''
Bob Hawkins Sr., president of Harvest House Publishers, said Friday.
   Based on interviews with Bush and his family, ``Man of
Integrity'' is being rushed into print in time for the Super
Tuesday primaries and caucuses on March 8. The 224-page book will
roll off the presses Monday.
