<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Chun Lookalike,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Actor Doffs Wig As President Departs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A popular television actor says he can
take his toupe off now that Chun Doo-hwan is no longer president.
   Park Yong-shik, 44, said Friday he was forced to wear a
hairpiece during Chun's seven-year term because he looks strikingly
like the balding former president, who was succeeded Thursday by
Roh Tae-woo.
   Park said he was banned from appearing on state-run television
in 1981 without explanation. Park said he found out later it was
because he resembled the 57-year-old Chun.
   In 1982, Park said, his proposal to wear a toupe and grow a
beard to change his appearance was accepted. However, he lost
important roles in soap operas and other programs and only received
minor parts in historical dramas.
   ``I hope such a comic thing will never happen again,'' Park said.
</TEXT>
