<HEAD>Snow Scattered Midwest and East</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in sections of the Midwest and East today, while rain
was widely scattered in the West.
   Snow showers were scattered across the lower Great Lakes region,
upper Ohio Valley and middle and northern Atlantic Coast.
   An advisory was in effect in parts of south central New York
state for up to 5 inches of snow today.
   Rain was scattered across California, Arizona, New Mexico and
southwest Texas.
   Skies were mostly cloudy from the Pacific Coast states through
Arizona to the southern Plains, and were partly cloudy over the
lower Mississippi Valley and Southeast. Fair skies prevailed across
most of the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for snow across the eastern Great Lakes
region and much of New England, and for scattered rain across the
lower Rio Grande valley, southern Texas and central mountains of
Arizona.
   Highs were expected to be in the 20s across the northern Great
Lakes and the northern half of New England; 30s and 40s from the
eastern Dakotas through the upper Mississippi and Ohio valleys into
southern New England; 70s across central and southern California,
from central and southern Oklahoma into Texas and the lower
Mississippi Valley and in the southern Atlantic Coast and Florida;
low to mid-80s in southern Arizona; and 50s to 60s across most of
the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 2
degrees at St. Johnsbury, Vt., to 66 at Brownsville and Corpus
Christi, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 44 fair; Boston 28 cloudy; Buffalo 31 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C., 37 fair; Cincinnati 40 fair; Cleveland 36 fair;
Detroit 30 fair; Miami 53 partly cloudy; New York 30 cloudy;
Philadelphia 33 cloudy; Pittsburgh 38 cloudy; Portland 16 fair;
Washington 32 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 29 fair; Chicago 37 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 57 cloudy; Denver 33 fair; Des Moines 34 fair;
Indianapolis 39 cloudy; Kansas City 39 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul
31 fair; Nashville 54 fair; New Orleans 51 fair; St. Louis 45 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 57 cloudy; Anchorage 22 cloudy; Las Vegas 62
cloudy; Los Angeles 65 partly cloudy; Phoenix 61 fair; Salt Lake
City 33 fair; San Diego 65 fair; San Francisco 58 foggy; Seattle 45
fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 14 fair; Toronto 28 snow.
