<HEAD>Motorist Stops, Finds Victim Was His Own Son</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A motorist on his way to work stopped to help
at an accident scene, only to discover the mortally injured victim
was his own 6-year-old son.
   ``I thought I was helping somebody else's kid,'' said Herbert L.
Robinson, a state employment specialist. ``I just saw him laying
there on the street and people standing around trying to take care
of him.''
   Mark and his 10-year-old sister, Joanna, were on their way to
school when the accident happened Friday, said their mother, Janet
Robinson.
   Police said the boy stopped to tie his shoe while walking with
two other children. When he hurried to catch up, he ran into an
intersection and was struck by a car.
   He died after being taken to Milwaukee County Medical Complex.
