<HEAD>Plastic Bag Mistaken For Bomb At Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police at Jan Smuts Airport
today blew up a plastic bag that they mistakenly believed contained
two limpet mines, authorities said.
   There were no injuries or damage in the controlled explosion,
police spokesman Col. Steve van Rooyen said.
   Van Rooyen said a woman reported seeing a plastic bag in an
unattented cart in the underground parking garage this morning.
Police, believing the bag contained a limpet mine and a mini-limpet
mine, took the bag onto a lawn outside the garage and destroyed it
using their own explosives, the spokesman added.
   Van Rooyen said the items destroyed were not limpet mines, but
were either limpet mine casings or imitation casings. He said that
the person who planted the bag had intended for it to be mistaken
as an explosive device.
   Jan Smuts Airport is the country's main airport, located east of
Johannesburg.
</TEXT>
