<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Father-Son Reunion,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Father-Son Reunion Occurs In Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was six months old when his
parents divorced 40 years ago has been reunited with his father in
the Pinellas County Jail.
   ``There were little tears in his eyes,'' Sheriff Gerry Coleman
said of inmate James Stewart Gaston. ``He was very affectionate
toward his son.''
   Gaston has been jailed for brief stays more than 1,400 times
because of alcohol-related misdemeanors. His son, James Stewart
Gallagher of Boston, learned his father was in the area from a
friend in Tampa who read about Gaston in the newspaper.
   Gaston, 65, was jailed Tuesday for 10 days for violating an open
alcohol container law.
   ``I've known him 30 years,'' the sheriff said. ``He probably was
my first arrest. When he's sober, he's the nicest man you've ever
met.''
   Gallagher, father of two young children, arrived Thursday and
Coleman arranged a 24-hour furlough for Gaston.
