<HEAD>Italian Porn Star Detained for 16 Hours</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Porn star Illona Staller, a member of
the Italian Parliament and candidate for the European Parliament,
was detained for 16 hours Saturday by police who accused her of
indecent exposure.
   Ms. Staller, known as Cicciolina, decided to cancel another
performance in Brussels and leave Belgium, said an organizer of her
tour. He quoted her as saying, ``I leave free but disapointed.''
   The nude performer was arrested early Saturday at the end of her
first night club appearance in Brussels after leaving the stage, a
police spokesman said. The spokesman, not identified in line with
police policy, said Cicciolina had overstepped the bounds of
decency, according to Belgian standards, and that she had been
warned in advance.
   She was taken to Brussels police headquarters and was released
at 6 p.m.
   Her spokesman said she had decided to interrupt her tour, which
included one more appearance in Brussels Saturday night and shows
in other cities, and to return to Italy.
   She also was making the tour to promote her candidacy for the
European Parliament in the 1989 election and to speak out in favor
of sexual freedom, said her spokesman, who talked with reporters on
the condition he not be identified.
   She was elected to the Italian Parliament last year as a
representative for the Radical Party. Marco Pannella, former
chairman of the party, said in a statement released here that the
police acted against her because she is a member of the Italian
Parliament.
   He said her arrest was ``obscene, not her show which I did not
see and in which I am not interested.'' He added he would protest
laws and regulations ``which hurt common sense and human rights.''
   The police spokesman declined to say if Cicciolina had been
asked to leave the country or if charges might be filed.
   A spokesman for the German airline Lufthansa said Ms. Staller
left Brussels on a flight to Frankfurt at 6:35 p.m.
