<HEAD>90-Year-Old Accused Of Killing Bride During Argument Over
Honeymoon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 90-year-old man has been accused of killing his
bride of less than a week during an argument over whether the
newlyweds should take a honeymoon cruise, police said Saturday.
   Vincenzo Quinto was booked on a charge of second-degree murder,
said Metro-Dade police spokesman Rey Valdes. Quinto was admitted to
a jail ward at Jackson Memorial Hospital because of his age, Valdes
added.
   Ana Quinto, 76, died Friday of ``blunt trauma to the head,''
Valdes said.
   Detective Pat Diaz said the couple met four months ago and
married one week ago Saturday. Quinto had moved to Miami a few
years ago after retiring from his job as a contractor in New York.
   Police on duty Saturday did not know if it was Quinto or his
wife who wanted to take a cruise.
