<HEAD>Reagan To Nominate Treasury Assistant Secretary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan intends to nominate Jill E.
Kent to be an assistant secretary of treasury for management, the
White House said Friday.
   Ms. Kent, a native of Detroit, would succeed John F. W. Rogers
in the Treasury Department post.
   Since 1985, Ms. Kent has been principal deputy assistant
secretary for finance and management at the Treasury Department.
Before that she was chief of the treasury and general services
branch at the Office of Management and Budget.
   She was acting chief of legislative reference at the Department
of Health and Human Services from 1978-80.
   Ms. Kent graduated from the University of Michigan in 1970 and
George Washington University law school in 1975.
