<NOTE>Eds: ADDS weekly price trends</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some price trends during the past week:
   Grains and soybean prices were mostly lower at the Chicago Board
of Trade.
   The contract for delivery of wheat in March settled at $3.15\ a
bushel Friday, down from $3.22 a week earlier; March corn settled
at 2.00} a bushel, up a notch over $2.00{ last Friday; March oats
settled Friday at $1.90\ a bushel, down from $1.91} a week earlier,
and March soybeans settled at $6.25{ a bushel, down from $6.31
   Cattle and hog futures prices were mixed at the Chicago
Mercantile Exchange.
   Live cattle for delivery in April settled at 72.55 cents a
pound, up from 72.37 cents a week earlier; March feeder cattle were
80.72 cents a pound, down from 83.55 cents last Friday; April hogs
settled Friday at 44.30 cents a pound, compared to 45.50 a week
earlier; and March frozen pork bellies dipped to 52.10 cents a
pound from 53.67 cents.
   Gold and silver prices retreated at the Commodity Exchange in
New York.
   April gold settled Friday at $431.10 a troy ounce, down from
$448 a week earlier; and March silver settled at $6.16 a troy
ounce, compared to $6.40 last Friday.
   Energy futures prices fell in trading at the New York Mercantile
Exchange.
   April crude oil settled Friday at $15.78 a barrel Friday, down
from $16.48 a week earlier; April heating oil was 43.37 cents a
gallon compared to 45.80 cents last Friday; and unleaded gasoline
dropped to 45.70 cents a gallon from 46.43 cents.
